hopobject.body: What do you like doing in your spare time? moduretic medscape "I don't feel very good to tell you the truth. I am glad we had the meeting. I appreciate it, but there are too many senators who don't understand the danger of the precedent of a Senate that can change the [rules] any time it wants to do anything it wants to," said Sen. Lamar Alexander, R-Tenn. "It might be a Democratic train going through the Senate now, but a year and a half from now, it might be the tea party express and some of them might not like that."
